67 #define CANTX_NUMBER_OF_MUX_VOLTAGES_PER_MESSAGE (4u)

69 /**
70  * CAN signals used in this message
71  * Parameters:
72  * bit start, bit length, factor, offset, minimum value, maximum value
73  */
74 static const CAN_SIGNAL_TYPE_s cantx_cellVoltageMultiplexer = {0u, 8u, 1.0f, 0.0f, 0.0f, 1.0f};
75 static const CAN_SIGNAL_TYPE_s cantx_cellVoltage0InvalidFlag = {8u, 1u, 1.0f, 0.0f, 0.0f, 1.0f};
76 static const CAN_SIGNAL_TYPE_s cantx_cellVoltage1InvalidFlag = {8u, 1u, 1.0f, 0.0f, 0.0f, 1.0f};
77 static const CAN_SIGNAL_TYPE_s cantx_cellVoltage2InvalidFlag = {10u, 1u, 1.0f, 0.0f, 0.0f, 1.0f};
78 static const CAN_SIGNAL_TYPE_s cantx_cellVoltage3InvalidFlag = {11u, 1u, 1.0f, 0.0f, 0.0f, 1.0f};
79 static const CAN_SIGNAL_TYPE_s cantx_cellVoltage0_mV = {12u, 13u, 1.0f, 0.0f, 0.0f, 8192.0f};
80 static const CAN_SIGNAL_TYPE_s cantx_cellVoltage1_mV = {25u, 13u, 1.0f, 0.0f, 0.0f, 8192.0f};
81 static const CAN_SIGNAL_TYPE_s cantx_cellVoltage2_mV = {38u, 13u, 1.0f, 0.0f, 0.0f, 8192.0f};
82 static const CAN_SIGNAL_TYPE_s cantx_cellVoltage3_mV = {51u, 13u, 1.0f, 0.0f, 0.0f, 8192.0f};

86 /*========== Static Function Prototypes =====================================*/
87 /**
88  * @brief Helper function for CANTX_CellVoltages()
89  *
90  * Used in the CANTX_CellVoltages() callback to set
91  * invalid flag data and voltage data
92  * in the CAN frame.
93  *
94  * @param[in] muxId multiplexer value
95  * @param[in] pMessage pointer to CAN frame data
96  * @param[in] cellVoltageSignal signal characteristics for voltage data
97  * @param[in] cellVoltageInvalidFlagSignal signal characteristics for invalid flag data
98  * @param[in] endianness big or little endianness of data
99  * @param[in] kpkCanShim shim to the database entries
100  */
101 static void CANTX_VoltageSetData(
102  uint8_t muxId,
103  uint64_t *pMessage,
104  CAN_SIGNAL_TYPE_s cellVoltageSignal,
105  CAN_SIGNAL_TYPE_s cellVoltageInvalidFlagSignal,
106  CAN_ENDIANNESS_e endianness,
107  const CAN_SHIM_s *const kpkCanShim);
108 
109 /*========== Static Function Implementations ================================*/
110 
111 static void CANTX_VoltageSetData(
112  uint8_t muxId,
113  uint64_t *pMessage,
114  CAN_SIGNAL_TYPE_s cellVoltageSignal,
115  CAN_SIGNAL_TYPE_s cellVoltageInvalidFlagSignal,
116  CAN_ENDIANNESS_e endianness,
117  const CAN_SHIM_s *const kpkCanShim) {
118  /* cell index must not be greater than the number of cells */
119  if (muxId < (BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_STRING * BS_NR_OF_STRINGS)) {
120  /* Get string, module and cell number */
121  const uint8_t stringNumber = DATA_GetStringNumberFromVoltageIndex(muxId);
122  const uint8_t moduleNumber = DATA_GetModuleNumberFromVoltageIndex(muxId);
123  const uint8_t cellNumber = DATA_GetCellNumberFromVoltageIndex(muxId);
124 
125  uint32_t signalData_valid = 0u;
126  /* Valid bits data */
127  if ((kpkCanShim->pTableCellVoltage->invalidCellVoltage[stringNumber][moduleNumber] & (0x01u << cellNumber)) ==
128  0u) {
129  signalData_valid = 0u;
130  } else {
131  signalData_valid = 1u;
132  }
133  /* Set valid bit data in CAN frame */
134  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(
135  pMessage,
136  cellVoltageInvalidFlagSignal.bitStart,
137  cellVoltageInvalidFlagSignal.bitLength,
138  signalData_valid,
139  endianness);
140 
141  /*Voltage data */
142  float_t signalData_mV =
143  (float_t)(kpkCanShim->pTableCellVoltage
144  ->cellVoltage_mV[stringNumber]
145  [(moduleNumber * BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_MODULE) + cellNumber]);
146  /* Apply offset and factor */
147  CAN_TxPrepareSignalData(&signalData_mV, cellVoltageSignal);
148  /* Set voltage data in CAN frame */
149  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(
150  pMessage, cellVoltageSignal.bitStart, cellVoltageSignal.bitLength, (uint32_t)signalData_mV, endianness);
151  }
152 }
153 
154 /*========== Extern Function Implementations ================================*/
155 extern uint32_t CANTX_CellVoltages(
156  CAN_MESSAGE_PROPERTIES_s message,
157  uint8_t *pCanData,
158  uint8_t *pMuxId,
159  const CAN_SHIM_s *const kpkCanShim) {
160  FAS_ASSERT(message.id == CANTX_CELL_VOLTAGES_ID);
161  FAS_ASSERT(message.idType == CANTX_CELL_VOLTAGES_ID_TYPE);
162  FAS_ASSERT(message.dlc == CAN_FOXBMS_MESSAGES_DEFAULT_DLC);
163  FAS_ASSERT(pCanData != NULL_PTR);
164  FAS_ASSERT(pMuxId != NULL_PTR);
165  FAS_ASSERT(kpkCanShim != NULL_PTR);
166  uint64_t messageData = 0u;
167 
168  /* Reset mux if maximum was reached */
169  if (*pMuxId >= (BS_NR_OF_STRINGS * BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_STRING)) {
170  *pMuxId = 0u;
171  }
172  /* First signal to transmit cell voltages: get database values */
173  if (*pMuxId == 0u) {
174  DATA_READ_DATA(kpkCanShim->pTableCellVoltage);
175  }
176 
177  /* Set mux signal in CAN frame */
178  uint32_t signalData = *pMuxId / CANTX_NUMBER_OF_MUX_VOLTAGES_PER_MESSAGE;
179  CAN_TxSetMessageDataWithSignalData(
180  &messageData,
181  cantx_cellVoltageMultiplexer.bitStart,
182  cantx_cellVoltageMultiplexer.bitLength,
183  (uint32_t)signalData,
184  message.endianness);
185 
186  /* Set other signals in CAN frame */
187  CANTX_VoltageSetData(
188  *pMuxId, &messageData, cantx_cellVoltage0_mV, cantx_cellVoltage0InvalidFlag, message.endianness, kpkCanShim);
189  /* Increment multiplexer for next cell */
190  (*pMuxId)++;
191  CANTX_VoltageSetData(
192  *pMuxId, &messageData, cantx_cellVoltage1_mV, cantx_cellVoltage1InvalidFlag, message.endianness, kpkCanShim);
193  /* Increment multiplexer for next cell */
194  (*pMuxId)++;
195  CANTX_VoltageSetData(
196  *pMuxId, &messageData, cantx_cellVoltage2_mV, cantx_cellVoltage2InvalidFlag, message.endianness, kpkCanShim);
197  /* Increment multiplexer for next cell */
198  (*pMuxId)++;
199  CANTX_VoltageSetData(
200  *pMuxId, &messageData, cantx_cellVoltage3_mV, cantx_cellVoltage3InvalidFlag, message.endianness, kpkCanShim);
201  /* Increment multiplexer for next cell */
202  (*pMuxId)++;
203 
204  /* All signal data copied in CAN frame, now copy data in the buffer that will be use to send the frame */
205  CAN_TxSetCanDataWithMessageData(messageData, pCanData, message.endianness);
206 
207  return 0;
208 }
